E NEDERLANDS BIBLIOTHEEK EN LEKTUUR CENTRUM (DUTCH LIBRARY AND LITERATURECENTRE) MEMBERS' MEETING, 11TH DECEMBER 1980' A PERSONAL IMPRESSION.REPORT OF THE MEETING OF NBLC MEMBERS IN AMSTERDAM, 11 DEC 80. TOPICSDISCUSSED INCLUDED CUTBACKS IN FINANCIAL SUPPORT FROM THE GOVERNMENT FORPUBLIC LIBRARY SERVICES IN THE NETHERLANDS, RAISING OF LIBRARY MEMBERSHIPCHARGES, AND REDUCTION OF THE AGE-LIMIT FOR FREE LIBRARY MEMBERSHIP. ALTHOUGHMANY OF THOSE PRESENT WERE OPPOSED TO A REDUCTION IN LIBRARY SERVICES SOMEFELT THAT THE GROWTH OF RECENT YEARS, IF ALLOWED TO CONTINUE, COULD LEAD TO AREDUCTION IN THE QUALITY OF SERVICES. THE QUESTION OF ALLOWING THE PUBLIC AGREATER VOICE IN THE RUNNING OF PUBLIC LIBRARIES AND THE POSITION OF UNPAIDVOLUNTARY STAFF WERE ALSO DISCUSSED